<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="060" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>E2E smoke test: Compose UI button → BFF → consumer routing → Document Summary playbook → result</title>
    <phase>Phase 6: E2E Smoke Test</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <tags>testing, integration-test, ai, e2e-test</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tests existing surface end-to-end (no new components added); ADR-038 testing rules apply; cross-phase dependency.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Cross-phase dependency: requires Phase 1 (Dataverse rows + JPS scopes) AND Phase 2 (BFF endpoint 026) AND Phase 4 (UI button 043) all complete — sequential gate after multiple phases converge.</parallel-reason>
    <dependencies>010,011,012,026,043</dependencies>
    <blocks>061</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Execute an end-to-end smoke test of the `compose-summarize` round-trip — the single most important R1 acceptance signal. Manually drive the Compose UI button (from Phase 4 task 043), which calls the BFF `/api/compose/action/compose-summarize` endpoint (from Phase 2 task 026), which uses `IConsumerRoutingService` (wired by task 011) to resolve the Document Summary playbook id, dispatches via `IInvokePlaybookAi`, and returns the result back to the UI. Verify the entire pipeline produces a coherent summary result and renders it in Compose. This task is MANUAL + LIGHT — it does NOT add the automated regression test (that's task 061), only verifies the wiring works.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    QA engineer + integration tester comfortable with the full Spaarke stack: SpaarkeAi UI, BFF endpoints, consumer-routing facade, JPS playbooks, and Dataverse. Capable of capturing telemetry / log spans across all layers for a pipeline trace.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A manual end-to-end smoke test that verifies the `compose-summarize` pipeline works: UI button click in Compose triggers BFF endpoint, which routes via `IConsumerRoutingService` to the Document Summary playbook (id `47686eb1-9916-f111-8343-7c1e520aa4df`), receives a result via `IInvokePlaybookAi`, and renders it in Compose. Result published as `notes/smoke-tests/compose-summarize-roundtrip.md` with screenshots, log spans, and verification of each pipeline hop.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-working">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-context">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-index">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Pipeline MUST use the AI PublicContracts facade (`IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi`) — verify in BFF logs that NO direct AI internals (`IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookService`) are injected into the Compose-side code path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Manual smoke-test write-up is an integration-test artifact; do NOT add `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration tests, or ctor null-check tests as part of this task (forbidden categories). Automated test artifact is task 061's scope, not this task's.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test a REAL Document Summary playbook execution against a REAL document (not a stub). Document id can be a small test document but must exist in the target environment.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Capture log spans across all four hops: UI → BFF → consumer routing → playbook → result.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>integration-test, ai-routing, compose, e2e</topic>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/InvokePlaybookAi.cs</file>
      <file>docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify all prerequisites are present in the target environment: workspace layout row (task 010), playbook consumer row (task 011), JPS scopes (task 012), BFF endpoint deployed (task 026), Compose UI button rendered (task 043). If any prereq is missing, STOP and flag the blocker.</step>
    <step order="2">Prepare a small test document — a real `sprk_document` with SPE content (1–3 pages of text the Document Summary playbook can summarize coherently).</step>
    <step order="3">Open Compose (workspace picker → "Compose"), load the test document via "Open in Compose" command bar (Path A). Verify the document mounts in the TipTap editor.</step>
    <step order="4">Click the `compose-summarize` UI button. Observe network tab: confirm a POST to `/api/compose/action/compose-summarize` with the expected JPS scope payload (`compose-document` shape from task 012).</step>
    <step order="5">In Application Insights (or BFF logs), trace the request: `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync` returns `47686eb1-9916-f111-8343-7c1e520aa4df`; `IInvokePlaybookAi` invokes the playbook; playbook returns a result.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify the result renders back in Compose (per Phase 4 UI task) and is coherent (a real summary of the document content, not an error or stub).</step>
    <step order="7">Write up findings in `notes/smoke-tests/compose-summarize-roundtrip.md`: include screenshots, log span IDs, end-to-end latency (per NFR-03 &lt;3s), and confirmation that no AI internals were leaked to the Compose CRUD path (per ADR-013).</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md status from 🔲 to ✅; reset current-task.md to next pending task (061).</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/smoke-tests/compose-summarize-roundtrip.md</output>
    <output type="notes">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/ — any deviation notes</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke test passes; full pipeline verified (per spec.md FR-11 Acceptance column: "Smoke test passes; full pipeline verified").</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">End-to-end latency ≤ 3s for typical legal document (per NFR-03).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF logs confirm only `IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi` were injected into the Compose-side code path (no `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` leakage per ADR-013).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke-test write-up published in `notes/smoke-tests/compose-summarize-roundtrip.md`.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This task is the single most important R1 acceptance signal. If any hop fails, flag the failing component and STOP — do NOT add workarounds in this task. Workarounds belong in the failing-component's task (e.g., re-open task 011 or 026). Automated regression test for this round-trip is task 061's scope, NOT this task — keep this one focused on manual verification + telemetry capture.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Before starting this task, load all files listed in &lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;. Follow the task-execute skill for mandatory pre-execution checklist, then proceed through the &lt;steps&gt; sequence.
    </protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
